  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2005-03-03",
    "date": "2005-03-22T18:52:51Z",
    "text": "Electronic Waste Recycling Promotion and Consumer Protection Act - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow waste recyclers and individual consumers a tax credit for recycling qualified electronic waste. Defines \"qualified electronic waste\" as any discarded computer display screen or system unit.\n\nBans the disposal of electronic waste without recycling three years after the enactment of this Act.\n\nRequires the head of each Federal executive agency to recycle electronic waste.\n\nRequires the Administrator of the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) to study the feasibility of establishing a nationwide recycling program for electronic waste that preempts any State recycling program."
  },
